<Content>Best kept secret/great value/kid friendly My 10 month old son, my 9 year old son, my husband and myself stayed at the Ilima from June 28th through July 6th on the 15th floor in room 1504.We had a view of the ocean. Waikiki is very noisy at nite so it was great to be up high. To offset the noise at nite we kept the AC fan running. The room was just like the pictures. The only rust was on the outside of the refrigerator door.The room was very clean, the staff was friendly and we were centrally located with only a five minute walk to the beach, shopping and Starbucks.Around the corner from us on Kuhio street is a Chilli's restaurant and across the street is a Food Pantry where we restocked diapers, formula and baby food. The room has pots, pans, dishes, dish soap, and utensils, so we were able to do a quick breakfast very easily. You can also go to the seaside grill in the morning and get pancakes and eggs as a take out for only $2.99. The hotel provided towels and beach mats at the desk daily. We rented an intermediate size car and were able to always find a parking spot.I would suggest a lite foldup stroller with a strap so you can carry it on the beach over your shoulder. Also pack a fold up beach ummbrella as they cost $30 at the stores or you can rent one in front of the hotels for $15 a day. The Ilima hotel pool is very nice. It is extremely windy so take the kids in the afternoon to the pool. The elevators are very fast. Also the carpets are very clean in the room so little babies stay clean. The guard railings appear safe and sturdy but I never let my kids near them. We got a better rate using our AAA discount and paying the extra $10 per kid per day. It was roughly $155 per day which included all the taxes and misc fees. They also have room safes bolted into the floor of your room which was very helpful as Waikiki has there share of beach comer pick pockets.To get to the beach walk down the street throught the International Market Place, then across the street through Dukes Restaurant located inside the Hotel. Wallmart is down by AlaMoana shopping center and they have great boggie boards for $20-30.ALOHA!!!!!!!!!!!! 
